The paper discusses a class of models that extend non-relational graph attention mechanisms to incorporate relational information, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates the models on molecular properties, which suggests a possible application in computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
